Liquidity and Capital Resources
Our principal sources of liquidity are our cash and cash equivalents and cash generated from operations, proceeds from issuance of
debt and common stock, financing leases, the sale of certain receivables, financing arrangements of vendor payables which
effectively extend payment terms and the Revolving Credit Facility (as defined below). Further, the incurrence of additional
indebtedness may inhibit our ability to incur new debt under the terms governing our existing and future indebtedness, which may
make it more difficult for us to incur new debt in the future to finance our business strategy.
